						<summary>

						<p>A slab in the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>16th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription can be dated to the 16th century on Palaeographical grounds.</p>						

						<p>Mutilated and damaged. Seems to register some gifts of land in Ghaṇḍikōṭa-sīma and also refers to the digging of canal by Kāmpus.</p>						

						</summary>
